author: KRISTOFER CRANE
title: The Bold and The beautiful cast arrive in Sydney | Daily Telegraph
text:
Katherine Kelly Lang says she’d be lost without her job Suits stars have taken to Australia’s bawdy humour WHAT an entrance! Fans went crazy at Sydney Airport this morning, as the famous stars of The Bold and The Beautiful arrived from LA.
The US soap which has been running for over 30 years will film Down Under over the next few days.
Big names including Jacqueline MacInnes, Rena Sofer, Don Diamont, John McCook and Heather Tom, stopped to pose with diehard fans, before heading into Sydney’s heat.
Before their arrival this morning the show’s executive producer and head writer Bradley Bell said the cast and crew were excited to return to Australia after filming here nearly 10 years ago.
media_camera Jacqueline MacInnes cut a stylish figure as she dazzled through customs. media_camera The star wore a fashionable tracksuit with mid-drift top showing off her toned torso. media_camera MacInnes was happy to pose with snap-happy fans.
“Collaborating with Qantas, Network Ten and CBS, viewers will witness romance, high style, jaw-dropping twists, harrowing stunts and major cliffhangers, all hallmarks of The Bold and The Beautiful,” he said.
media_camera Rena Sofer arrived glowing. media_camera The star was all smiles as she posed with fans. media_camera Don Diamont looking surprisingly refreshed after his long-haul flight.
The cast members will also take part in a sold-out Q&A session at Parramatta’s Riverside Theatre this time on Sunday.
They are not the only international TV stars in Sydney at the moment.
Suits actors Sarah Rafferty and Rick Hoffman have been in Australia for the past few days.
media_camera Schae Harrison made a bright entry into Sydney. media_camera Katherine Kelly Lang ready to brave the heat. media_camera Longstanding soap star John McCook. media_camera Scott Clifton was happy to strike a pose. media_camera Thorsten Kaye was among the cast to arrive in Sydney. media_camera Heather Tom flashed her pearly whites for fans.
